	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I thought I'd give some info about the project and the album and band I'm covering.
<br />
<br />Colony was released by a band called In Flames in 1999.
<br />In Flames has been around/formed since about 1990, with their first album in 1994, and are still an active band to this day.
<br />
<br />They are considered to be a "founding band" of the genre many call Melodic Death Metal/Melodeath, which takes heavy influence from NWOBHM, Iron Maiden, Thrash, Speed, and Death metal to form a new blend of music.
<br />
<br />Colony was their 4th album, and their first to feature their most well known line up, until the founder Jesper Stromblad quit the band.
<br />
<br />
<br />The project is being done entirely from scratch and by ear.
<br />
<br />The first 2 channels will be utilized mostly for rhythm guitars.
<br />The triangle channel will be used as bass,
<br />The noise is used for mostly high end percussion.
<br />The DPCM channel will be mostly for drum samples which were rendered in Reaper using Addictive Drums: Bass drum, snare, tom.
<br />It will also be used for voice samples.
<br />
<br />VRC6 channels:
<br />square channels will be used for lead guitar parts, and some synth parts.
<br />saw channel will be used for synth parts.
<br />
<br />The music will be available in formats:
<br />nsf
<br />nsfe
<br />mp3

		

		</td>
	</tr>
